title: Lorry overturns, killing driver and attendant - Nation | The Star Online
text:
SEREMBAN: A lorry laden with frozen processed chicken overturned at KM36 of Jalan Bahau-Kemayan near Jempol early Sunday, killing the Bangladeshi driver and an attendant.    
Another attendant was seriously injured, said Jempol OCPD Supt Noorzainy Mohd Noor.    
He identified the dead men as driver Tanvir Ahammed Siddique, 46, and Ismail Fadlizah, also 46. 
The injured attendant was identified as Mohd Syaaban Mohd Amin, 29, who has been sent to the Jempol Hospital, he said.    
Supt Noorzainy said the accident happened at about 5.30am when the lorry veered off at a sharp bend and overturned on the road shoulder, trapping Tanvir and Ismail in the crushed driver's cabin.    
"Tanvir and Ismail died on the spot," he said.    
Supt Noorzainy said a check on the lorry showed that the vehicle had eight summonses for speeding between 2013 and 2015.    
The bodies of Tanvir and Ismail were also sent to the Jempol Hospital, he said. - Bernama
